qas.question: What is the name of a common alloy?
What is something on a car that sometimes is made of alloy?
Steel and other very practical metals are also named what?
Aluminum alloy is sometimes used as a synonym for what?
Why are some items made of iron only referred to by name?

context: The term "alloy" is sometimes used in everyday speech as a synonym for a particular alloy. For example, <a1_0>automobile wheels<a1_0/> made of an aluminium alloy are commonly referred to as simply "<b3_0>alloy wheels<b3_0/>", although in point of fact steels and most other metals in practical use are also <a2_0>alloys<a2_0/>. <a0_0>Steel<a0_0/> is <b4_0>such a common alloy<b4_0/> that many items made from it, like wheels, barrels, or girders, are simply referred to by the name of the item, assuming it is made of steel. When made from other materials, they are typically specified as such, (i.e.: "bronze wheel," "plastic barrel," or "wood girder").
